The paper deals with the problem of matchmaking in electronic marketplaces and web services, which involves discovering the best available offers to a given request. The approach is based on Description Logics, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence and Knowledge Representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents non-monotonic inferences and complexity results, which are related to Logic and Computation (cs.LO). The algorithms proposed for semantic matchmaking are based on reasoning about concepts and their relationships, which is a typical task in Database Systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed framework as a mediator in e-marketplaces, which involves issues related to Computer Engineering (cs.CE) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
